{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 23:16:05.127678", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission completed.\n\nSummary of submitted solution:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- Faulty devices localized:\n  - server_access_router\n  - load_balancer (10.200.0.7)\n  - web_server_0 (10.200.0.3)\n  - web_server_1 (10.200.0.4)\n  - web_server_2 (10.200.0.5)\n  - web_server_3 (10.200.0.6)\n- Root cause(s) selected:\n  - ospf_area_misconfiguration (represents lack of intended segmentation / access control at the server edge — server subnet advertised and reachable)\n  - sender_application_delay (represents backend web server processing delays causing high TTFB)\n  - load_balancer_overload (represents potential additional processing/queuing at the load balancer)\n\nIf you want, next steps I can take:\n- Run FRR config and ACL checks on server_access_router and adjacent devices to confirm and, if desired, propose ACLs or VRF changes to re-establish intended segmentation.\n- Run per-backend HTTP timing, concurrency/load tests, and resource monitoring (CPU/memory) on web servers and the load balancer to pinpoint which component(s) are causing the application latency.\n- Produce concrete mitigation steps (example ACLs, load balancer tuning, web server configuration changes) once you confirm which of the suggested next checks you'd like me to run.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2429, "output_tokens": 302, "total_tokens": 2731, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
